<center><table border=0><tr><td><center><H2><font face=arial>I heard it both ways...</font></H2></center>
<font face=arial size=2><b>Posted By:</b> <A HREF="/cgi-local/whois2.cgi?Holly Golightly">Holly Golightly</a><br>
<b>Posted On:</b> 5:52 p.m. 27/3/1999<br>
<b>Subject:</b> I heard it both ways...<p>
<br><center><img src="http://www.everworld.net/pvpquest/images/divider.gif" width=452 height=22 border=0></center><BR><P ALIGN=CENTER><b>In Reply To:</b> <A HREF="http://www.everworld.net/cgi-local/pvp.cgi?read=1751" TARGET=_self>Geiger: Looting of players killed by monsters, bug or feature?</A> (Min)
</STRONG><FONT SIZE=2 color=#FFFFFF FACE=arial>
<P>I've heard Brad is going to "fix" the looting. And I've heard he likes it the way it is.

<P>This is a topic of hot debate. Some think it is a feature. Others think it is a "bug", ripe for abuse and twinking. I tend to agree with the latter, that it is abused by a number of players.
<P>Other than rumors, I'm not sure Brad has made an official announcement on the matter. I sure would like to see one though.
<P>Holly Golightly.
</FONT></td></tr></table></P>
